<p>Note: 1. p.m. – <i>pro memoria</i>, i.e. for the record/for future reference</p><p><b>2.7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Production refunds for sugar used in the chemical industry</b></p><p>Formerly, financial assistance was provided to the chemical industry to balance the higher price of EU sugar. However, as part of the reform process, access to out-of-quota sugar at world market prices was allowed for the chemical industry, doing away with the need for such assistance.</p><p>Table 2.7.1: Appropriations and outturns (in €)</p><table class="renderedtable" border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0">
